{{see|vía}}
==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈvi:ə/, /ˈvaɪə/}}

===Etymology 1===
From Latin [[#Latin|via]] ‘road’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A main road or highway, especially in ancient Rome.  ''(Mainly used in set phrases, below.)''

====Derived terms====
{{top2}}
*[[via affirmativa]]
*[[Via Crucis]]
*[[Via Dolorosa]]
{{mid2}}
*[[Via Lactea]]
*[[via media]]
*[[via negativa]]
{{bottom}}

===Etymology 2===
From Latin [[#Latin|via]], ablative singular of [[#Latin|via]] ‘way, road’ (Etymology 1, above).

====Preposition====
'''via'''

# By way of; passing through.

====Translations====
*German: [[über]] ''accusative''

